history.content:
Same reply as on FB:

"If the CS conflict form is processed when there is open space in the class, then you could still get in.
But otherwise (and for non-EECS courses where the department advisors aren't taking on this extra work of manually enrolling students), yes, using the SIS time conflict form on 61C which has open space would be the "normal" way of doing it."

I'm not a declared CS major yet but I enrolled in CS 170 phase 1 as I knew I wanted to take it this spring semester. I'm going to be declared this semester but as CS majors get priority, I was placed on the waitlist (and am currently in position 4 on the lecture waitlist). However, I am also currently enrolled in CS 61C. Does this mean that it is basically impossible for me to get into CS 170 as I have it waitlisted AND I have a time conflict? As I understand, someone has to manually accept me from the CS time conflict sheet, but because I am waitlisted and there is a time conflict, I will automatically get passed over? (in reference to @5621) Or am I still ok to get into cs 170 if I fill out the CS time conflict form right now? 

I guess a possible solution woul dbe to drop 61C until i get into 170 off waitlist, and then re-enroll w/ the form, would this be the best solution?
history.subject: Impossible to get into CS170?
